    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a lineup optimized for high-upside matchups, led by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (77.02) and **Junior Caminero** (76.66). **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Tobias Myers, with his dynamic platoon advantage driving a +14% score boost, making him our primary target for stolen base production. Meanwhile, **Junior Caminero** is positioned to capitalize on favorable wind conditions and a strong spot in the two-hole against Mitch Keller, providing an elite floor despite a tough park factor. We are also leaning heavily on **Trea Turner** (69.15) and **Yordan Alvarez** (67.90); **Trea Turner** remains a cornerstone of our offense due to his premium lead-off spot, while **Yordan Alvarez** continues to demonstrate elite xwOBA metrics that keep his production high even when facing a left-handed pitcher like Matthew Liberatore.\n\nWe have a heightened alert for the outfield, where **Carson Benge** (63.27) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** carry a 34% rain risk, which may necessitate rapid adjustments if the Chicago-area weather deteriorates. On the bench, the decision to sit **Victor Scott II** (47.23) was the most difficult; while his speed is vital to our strategy, the optimizer sidelined him due to a suppressed projection stemming from a projected nine-hole batting position and a challenging matchup against Mike Burrows. Consequently, we have opted for the superior individual efficiency scores of **Hyeseong Kim** (62.92) and **Chase Meidroth** (63.19), both of whom are projected to deliver more immediate value in the 5x5 categories. We will monitor the lineup postings for **Dillon Dingler** and **Gary Sanchez** closely, as any shift from their projected spots will force a recalibration of our catcher efficiency targets against high-tier arms like Garrett Crochet and Eury P\u00e9rez.",
